20#ifndef GCC_VALUE_PROF_H
21#define GCC_VALUE_PROF_H
22
23/* Supported histogram types. */
24enum hist_type
25{
26 HIST_TYPE_INTERVAL, /* Measures histogram of values inside a specified
27 interval. */
28 HIST_TYPE_POW2, /* Histogram of power of 2 values. */
29 HIST_TYPE_SINGLE_VALUE, /* Tries to identify the value that is (almost)
30 always constant. */
31 HIST_TYPE_INDIR_CALL, /* Tries to identify the function that is (almost)
32 called in indirect call */
33 HIST_TYPE_AVERAGE, /* Compute average value (sum of all values). */
34 HIST_TYPE_IOR, /* Used to compute expected alignment. */
35 HIST_TYPE_TIME_PROFILE, /* Used for time profile */
36 HIST_TYPE_INDIR_CALL_TOPN, /* Tries to identify the top N most frequently
37 called functions in indirect call. */
38 HIST_TYPE_MAX
39};
40
41#define COUNTER_FOR_HIST_TYPE(TYPE) ((int) (TYPE) + GCOV_FIRST_VALUE_COUNTER)
42#define HIST_TYPE_FOR_COUNTER(COUNTER) \
43 ((enum hist_type) ((COUNTER) - GCOV_FIRST_VALUE_COUNTER))
44
45
46/* The value to measure. */
47struct histogram_value_t
48{
49 struct
50 {
51 tree value; /* The value to profile. */
52 gimple *stmt; /* Insn containing the value. */
53 gcov_type *counters; /* Pointer to first counter. */
54 struct histogram_value_t *next; /* Linked list pointer. */
55 } hvalue;
56 enum hist_type type; /* Type of information to measure. */
57 unsigned n_counters; /* Number of required counters. */
58 struct function *fun;
59 union
60 {
61 struct
62 {
63 int int_start; /* First value in interval. */
64 unsigned int steps; /* Number of values in it. */
65 } intvl; /* Interval histogram data. */
66 } hdata; /* Profiled information specific data. */
67};
68
69typedef struct histogram_value_t *histogram_value;
70typedef const struct histogram_value_t *const_histogram_value;
71
72
73typedef vec<histogram_value> histogram_values;
